. The observed high [Mn/Fe] ratios in Sculptor and Carina\nmay also require additional enrichment from pure deflagrations, possibly as\nType Iax supernovae. Future observations of dSph stars will provide more\nstringent constraints on the progenitor systems and explosion mechanism of SNe\nIa.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 24 Jun 2019 14:11:36 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 10 Mar 2020 17:57:06 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 27 Apr 2020 16:54:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-06-10"}
